LLC_BI__lookupKey__c
lookupKey
Text(255) (External ID) (Unique Case Insensitive)
true
true
This field is optional. If populated, the value must be unique across all the records of this type. The field typically contains an external identifier that is used to associate the record with its matching record in an external system. The field can also be used to efficiently associate related records, when importing data into nCino, without the need to know the internal ID for the record. For more information, refer to https://developer.salesforce.com/docs/atlas.en-us.apexcode.meta/apexcode/langCon_apex_dml_nested_object.html

For more information, refer to https://developer.salesforce.com/docs/atlas.en-us.apexcode.meta/apexcode/langCon_apex_dml_nested_object.htm

Is Syndication Agent
Checkbox
false
false
This field is not required and is manually populated. When true, this field indicates that the product this feature is for is a syndicated loan (which is a bank facility that is offered by a group of lenders). Additionally, it indicates that the financial institution this product feature is for is the primary agent of the syndicated loan. The agent is a lead bank or underwriter of the loan, known as the arranger, the agent or the lead lender. This lender may put up a proportionally bigger share of the loan, or it may perform duties such as dispersing cash flows among the other syndicate members and administrative tasks.

LLC_BI__Line_Of_Credit__c
Line Of Credit
Checkbox
false
false
This field is manually selected. When enabled, this product feature specifies that a product is a line of credit. This flag is used to override the relationship stats criteria "UsePrincipalBalance=true", so that a line of credit product always uses "Original Amount" for exposure calculations. Additionally, the LLC_BI__Current_LTV__c on Loan uses Original Amount for its calculation. When disabled, the relationship stats criteria is not overwritten, and an exposure calculation with "UsePrincipalBalance=true" criteria will use the principal balance. Similarly, LLC_BI__Current_LTV__c will use principal balance for its calculation. By default, this is disabled.

LLC_BI__Overdraft_Consent__c
Overdraft Consent
Picklist
true
false
This picklist field is populated during the deposit account opening process. This field indicates the decision made by the customer to either request or refuse institution overdraft services that include and cover overdraft activity on ATM and everyday debit card transactions as part of standard overdraft services. The statement that reflects the customer's decision will be preceded by an X to indicate the selection. The statement not selected is preceded by a short line segment. The picklist value options are: 1/ Request overdraft service on ATM and everyday debit card transactions; and 2/ Refuse overdraft service on ATM and everyday debit card transactions.

false
This field is optional. It is populated by a user or a data integration. The beneficial owner is a sponsored Foreign Financial Institution (FII) without a GIIN number prior to 1/1/16 for purposes of IRS forms W-8 and certifies either (1) that it is an FFI only because it is an investment entity and has an agreement for sponsorship; or (2) that it is a controlled foreign corporation 'as defined by section 957(a).'
